  <description><![CDATA[<p>Which three words would best describe the Adler Spa Resort Sicilia? Spacious, soothing and sustainable.</p>
<p>This is a brand new hotel, so you just know it's been built with all of the modern day comforts in mind. This is such a great place to stay if you want a peaceful holiday, away from the hustle and bustle of the city. The huge infinity pool and private beach mean that you can relax outside all day.</p>
<p>If you can't get enough of history, then you're only a stones throw away from lots of important historical landmarks. You can visit the Valley of the Temples which is a UNESCO world heritage site and the Selinute archaeological park in Agrigento (the biggest in Europe). Who needs the Parthenon when you have Agrigento's Bouleuterion (an Ancient Greek senate house)?</p>
<p>After a long day on your feet, come back to the hotel spa and try out the massage room which overlooks the sea. End your day by admiring the Sicilian coast-line and drinking wine on the terrace at sunset- you can't get more relaxing than that.</p>
<p>Car hire is recommended for this hotel. Transfer time is approx. 2.5 hours from Catania Airport and 2 hours from Palermo airport.</p>]]></description>
